#15 What are text formatting tags in HTML?
HTML provides several tags to format text, both visually (how the text looks on the page) and semantically (what the text means).
| Tag        | Meaning                                          | Example                         |
| ---------- | ------------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------- |
| `<b>`      | Makes text **bold** (visual only)                | `<b>Bold text</b>`              |
| `<strong>` | Emphasizes text as *important* (semantic + bold) | `<strong>Important!</strong>`   |
| `<i>`      | Italic text (visual only)                        | `<i>Italic text</i>`            |
| `<em>`     | Emphasized text as *important* (semantic + italic)              | `<em>Really!</em>`              |
| `<u>`      | Underlines text                                  | `<u>Underlined text</u>`        |
| `<small>`  | Makes text smaller                               | `<small>Small text</small>`     |
| `<mark>`   | Highlights text                                  | `<mark>Highlighted text</mark>` |

#16 What is the difference between <b> and <strong> (and between <i> and <em>)?
<b> and <i> are styling tags (visual emphasis).
<strong> and <em> carry semantic meaning, telling browsers and screen readers that the text is important or stressed.

#17 How do you create a hyperlink?
Use the <a> (anchor) tag with the href attribute to specify the link‚Äôs destination.
<a href="https://www.google.com">Visit Google</a>

#18 How do you link to another page in the same project?
You can use relative paths.
In index.html: <a href="about.html">Go to About Page</a>

#19 how to switch to a new line in HTML?
Pressing Enter in HTML code does not guarantee a new line in the browser.
Use <br> for line breaks or block-level elements for larger sections of text.

The <br> tag goes exactly where you want the line to break.
Usually, it is placed at the end of the line that should end, before the text that should start on a new line.
It should not be at the very beginning of a block (unless you want the first line to start with a blank line).

#20 How do you create an email link?
Use the mailto: protocol inside the href (Hypertext REFerence.)
‚Äúmail to‚Äù, meaning: ‚ÄúSend an email to this address.‚Äù

#21 How do you create a list in HTML?
There are two main types:
Unordered list (<ul>) ‚Äî bullet points
Ordered list (<ol>) ‚Äî numbered

<ul>
  <li>Apples</li>
  <li>Bananas</li>
</ul>

<ol>
  <li>First</li>
  <li>Second</li>
</ol>

#22 What are nested lists?
Lists can be placed inside other lists.
<ul>
  <li>Fruits
    <ul>
      <li>Apple</li>
      <li>Banana</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Vegetables</li>
</ul>

#23 How do you create a line break and a horizontal line?
<br> = Line break (moves text to a new line)
<hr> = Horizontal rule (draws a line across the page)

#24 How do you add an image?
<img src="cat.jpg" alt="An image of a cute cat">

Required: Specifies the path to the image.

Can be:
Relative path (image in same folder): "cat.jpg"
Relative path in another folder: "images/cat.jpg"
Absolute URL: "https://example.com/cat.jpg"

#25 Difference between links
You need the direct URL of the image, which usually ends with an image file extension like .jpg, .png, or .gif

